Backup Encryption Key
=====================

⚠️ SECURITY WARNING ⚠️
This file previously contained an actual backup encryption key that was exposed in a
public GitHub repository. The key has been rotated and all backups re-encrypted as of
January 1, 2026.

Encryption Key: [REDACTED - Stored in KeePass and offline secure location]

NEVER commit encryption keys to version control.

To generate new encryption key:
```bash
openssl rand -base64 32 > /root/backup-encryption-key.txt
chmod 600 /root/backup-encryption-key.txt
```

Key Storage Requirements (NIST 800-171 MP-5):
1. Store in KeePass password database
2. Print hardcopy and store in physical safe
3. Store encrypted copy on offline USB drive in secure location
4. NEVER commit to Git repositories
5. NEVER store in cloud services
6. Rotate every 12 months or immediately if compromised

To re-encrypt existing backups with new key:
1. Decrypt with old key
2. Generate new key
3. Encrypt with new key
4. Securely wipe old encrypted backups
5. Update backup scripts with new key location
6. Test restore procedure with new key

Incident Response:
If this key is compromised:
1. Generate new encryption key immediately
2. Re-encrypt all backups with new key
3. Securely delete old encrypted backups
4. Document incident per IR policy
5. Report as NIST 800-171 security incident
